welcome party tonight, and they've invited
the entire neighborhood.

284
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,972
Oh, I simply adore entertaining.

285
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,933
Don't I just adore it, Jianyu?

286
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:34,146
Oh, yes, by the way,
Jianyu here is a Buddhist monk, you see,

287
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:36,857
and he obeys a strict code of silence.

288
00:13:37,274 --> 00:13:39,652
So when you see him smiling and nodding,

289
00:13:39,735 --> 00:13:42,696
that's actually his way of
jumping up and down with glee.

290
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:44,532
Isn't that right, darling?

291
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,493
So we'll see you tonight?

292
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:48,702
-Great.
-Yes.

293
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:51,539
[classical music playing]

294
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:54,291
-[chuckles]
-No way.

295
00:13:58,128 --> 00:13:59,922
My entire house could fit in this room.

296
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:02,341
Okay, uh...

297
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,342
Help me out here.

298
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:06,387
Tell me one good thing
that you did on Earth,

299
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:10,224
just one truly kind and decent act

300
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:13,102
so that I can feel better
about helping you out.

301
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,895
Uh...

302
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:17,022
Let's forget about good.

303
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:19,066
Um, just tell me something
neutral about yourself.

304
00:14:19,149 --> 00:14:21,068
Like, tell me about
the day before you died.

305
00:14:21,151 --> 00:14:22,236
What do you remember?

306
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,657
Hi there. Do you have a second
to talk about the environment?

307
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,325
Do you have a second to eat my farts?

308
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:30,286
You missed.

309
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,872
[scoffs] Pick it up
if you're so horny for the environment.

310
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,499
I don't remember anything specific.

311
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:36,959
-Oh...
-Look.

312
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:40,212
I might not have been a saint,
but it's not like I killed anybody.

313
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,589
I wasn't an arsonist.

314
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,507
I never found a wallet outside of an IHOP

315
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:46,093
and thought about returning it but
saw the owner lived out of state

316
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:49,138
so just took the cash
and dropped the wallet back on the ground.

317
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,431
Okay, that's really specific,

318
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:52,558
and that makes me think that
you definitely did do that.

319
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:56,562
All I'm saying is
these people might be "good,"

320
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:59,565
but are they really
that much better than me?

321
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,943
Well, I spent half my life in North Korea

322
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:06,196
fighting for women's rights
and the other half in Saudi Arabia

323
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,615
fighting for gay rights.

324
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:10,701
So we said, "If the UN
won't remove those land mines, we will."

325
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,621
And we dug up over a thousand
unexploded land mines

326
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,414
from the area surrounding the orphanage.

327
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:16,916
Well, then he said,

328
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,542
"You can't give me both
your kidneys, you'll die."

329
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,711
And I said, "But you will live."

330
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:23,964
And I know we just met on this bus
ten minutes ago, but he seemed nice.

331
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:26,300
Oh, forget it. Heading to the bar!

332
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:29,970
-[clinking glass]
-[applauding]

333
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:32,097
Thank you, thank you.

334
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:35,643
You all know that I am the
architect of this neighborhood.

335
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,561
But what you don't know is...

336
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,814
Golly, I'm not supposed
to tell you this, but, um...

337
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:42,733
Oh, what the heck?

338
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,402
This is actually
the very first neighborhood

339
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:47,112
that I have ever designed.

340
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:50,282
I had been an apprentice
for over 200 years,

341
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:54,828
and my boss has finally given me
my first solo project.

342
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:56,038
-[crowd exclaims]
-[chuckles]

343
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,998
Yes! [laughs]

344
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,335
Ah, ah, ah. Hold on there, ace.

345
00:16:01,418 --> 00:16:03,003
Let me get more of them shrampies.

346
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,505
-Okay, easy.
-What?

347
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:06,715
-They're for everybody, right?
-Yes, exactly.

348
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:09,927
[Michael] And you deserve a perfect world

349
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:12,930
because every single one of you

350
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:14,890
is a good person.

351
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:17,768
That's it for me. Back to you, Tahani.

352
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:21,063
-Bravo, Michael, bravo!
-Thank you.

353
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,232
And I would just like to quickly say

354
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:25,526
if any of you would like
to play tennis tonight,

355
00:16:25,609 --> 00:16:29,029
we have 36 regulation grass tennis courts.

356
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:31,407
Such fun. Cheers. [laughs]

357
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:35,202
Tahani, what a condescending bench.

358
00:16:35,285 --> 00:16:36,829
-Okay, okay, okay, okay.
-Am I right?

359
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:38,914
Why does she still have
that British accent, right?

360
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,541
No one else here has an accent.

361
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,292
-She's choosing to have that accent.
-[shushes]

362
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:45,254
[imitating Tahani] "Oh, hello.

363
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:49,550
I am just a big, beautiful,
utterly perfect cartoon giraffe."

364
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:53,095
Oh, okay. Okay.
I think it's time to go home.

365
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:55,097
Wait, wait, wait.
I just have to go upstairs

366
00:16:55,305 --> 00:16:57,433
real quick and steal
a bunch of gold stuff.

367
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,059
Okay, don't do that.

368
00:17:00,477 --> 00:17:02,604
Don't do... No, Eleanor, Eleanor, Eleanor.

369
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,568
Hello, creepy house that I hate.

370
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,362
Hello, one million clowns.

371
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,199
Why aren't there stairs here?

372
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:17,036
[grunts]

373
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,496
What kind of weirdo house is this?

374
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:21,623
Ooh.

375
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:25,294
Did you fill your bra with shrimp?

376
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:27,046
No. [hiccups]

377
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,756
Yes.

378
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:30,799
Whatever, it's freakin' heaven.

379
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,135
I'm sure they have plenty of shellfish.

380
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:36,055
That Tahani is a real butthead, huh?

381
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,639
[gasps] Hey.

382
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,600
At least I can still say "butthead."

383
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:41,560
Oh, she is a butthead.

384
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:43,437
Found some pajamas.

385
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:47,900
Chidi... Chidi, Chidi?

386
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:51,070
I'm sorry that you had
to deal with this...

387
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,031
It's okay.

388
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:56,450
It's not, though. [sighs]

389
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:58,619
Do you think anybody cared that I died?

390
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:02,164
Maybe someone did. I don't know.

391
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:03,874
I was an only child.

392
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:06,126
My parents were divorced when I was a kid.

393
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:10,214
They were both crummy people,
so they're probably... [exclaims]

394
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:11,924
In The Bad Place.

395
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,301
Maybe they're being used
to torture each other.

396
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,596
-It would work.
-[chuckles]

397
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,557
I bet way more people cared that you died.

398
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:24,895
'Cause you're a nice person.
[clears throat]

399
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:27,272
You're a nice person, Chidi...

400
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,233
Anaconda.

401
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,237
-"Anagonye."
-Aganocomonga.

402
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:34,780
"Anagonye."

403
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:36,615
-Ags... say it again.
-"Anagonye."

404
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:39,284
-No, say what you said before.
-I did. It's Anagonye.

405
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:41,954
-You just changed it.
-I didn't change it, it's my name.

406
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:43,956
Argrugande. Ariana Grande.

407
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,457
[gasps] That's a person.

408
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:46,583
I did it.

409
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:48,752
Good night.

410
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:51,463
Good night.

411
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:55,592
[circus music playing]

412
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:58,929
[recorded cheering]

413
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:01,181
Well, that's terrifying.

414
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,475
-[snoring]
-[birds cawing]

415
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:05,602
[lightning crackles]

416
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:09,398
[birds cawing]

417
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:11,692
[lightning crackles]

418
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:14,278
That can't be good.

419
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,283
["Break Free" playing]

420
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:29,001
[Eleanor] Oh, fork.

421
00:19:41,221 --> 00:19:42,556
-Michael.
-Hmm?

422
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:45,893
Is that giant, terrifying ladybug
supposed to be there?

423
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:48,395
Ah. Well, great question, Tahani.

424
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,855
No. No, it's not.

425
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:53,358
I have no idea why any of this
is happening or how to control it.

426
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:55,027
Should we run away then?

427
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:56,778
Yes.

428
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,947
Righto.

429
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:03,744
[growls]

430
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:20,469
Chidi, Chidi! What's going on?

431
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,179
Why are there giant animals everywhere?

432
00:20:22,596 --> 00:20:25,057
Do you hear Ariana Grande playing?

433
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:27,726
Why is everyone wearing blue and yellow?

434
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:29,811
You're not.

435
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:32,731
You're the only one who's not.

436
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:35,984
Eleanor, this is all happening
because of you.

437
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,487
Oh, fork me.

438
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:43,492
Okay, okay.
We don't know this is because of me.

439
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:46,453
Eleanor, this place is
a perfectly made Swiss watch,

440
00:20:46,536 --> 00:20:48,330
and you are a wrench in the gears.

441
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:51,667
Actually, you're a hammer,
just smashing the gears into dust.

442
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,920
Oh, hang on.
Not everybody here is perfect, okay?

443
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:56,546
Tahani is totally condescending.

444
00:20:56,630 --> 00:21:00,217
And there are a couple of,
you know, chunksters.

445
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,510
Oh, come on!

446
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:03,512
No judgment. I'm just saying

447
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:07,808
I'm not the only one with flaws.
So how can we be sure this is my fault?

448
00:21:07,891 --> 00:21:11,061
You hogged all the shrimp,
and now there are shrimp flying around.

449
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:14,856
You called Tahani a giraffe,
and now there are giraffes everywhere.

450
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,401
Okay, fine, turns out there are many ways
to know that it was me.

451
00:21:17,484 --> 00:21:19,486
Let's just face it, Eleanor,
you don't belong here.

452
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:24,449
Well, then this system sucks.

453
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:27,035
What, one in a million
gets to live in paradise

454
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:29,288
and everyone else
is tortured for eternity?

455
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,455
Come on.

456
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:34,376
I mean, I wasn't freaking Gandhi,
but I was okay.

457
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:37,504
I was a medium person.

458
00:21:37,587 --> 00:21:40,382
I should get to spend eternity
in a medium place!

459
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:42,050
Like Cincinnati.

460
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,303
Everyone who wasn't perfect
but wasn't terrible

461
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:46,430
should get to spend eternity
in Cincinnati.

462
00:21:46,513 --> 00:21:48,557
Look, apparently it doesn't work that way.

463
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:52,728
I'm sorry, Eleanor,
but there's nothing anyone can do.

464
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:55,897
Unless...

465
00:21:56,690 --> 00:22:00,819
There is something we can do.
Unless you could teach me.

466
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:03,864
-Teach you what?
-How to be good.

467
00:22:04,197 --> 00:22:07,576
{\an8}That was your job, right?
A professor of ethics?

468
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:09,870
{\an8}No one knew I was a problem
when I arrived.

469
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:11,455
{\an8}Things only started getting crazy

470
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:14,499
{\an8}after I was an ash-hole
to everyone at the party. Ugh.

471
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:18,628
{\an8}You know I'm trying to say "ash-hole"
and not "ash-hole," right?

472
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:19,880
{\an8}I got that, yes.

473
00:22:19,963 --> 00:22:23,216
{\an8}Okay, give me a chance.
Let me earn my place here.

474
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:26,887
{\an8}-Let me be your ethical guinea pig.
-[knocking on door]

475
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:30,057
{\an8}[Michael] Hey, guys! Uh...
Emergency neighborhood meeting, now!

476
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:31,516
{\an8}We'll be right there, Michael!

477
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,436
{\an8}If I walk out of here in these clothes,
I'm toast.

478
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:38,273
My soul is in your hands, soulmate.
What's it gonna be?

479
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:40,233
[knocking continues]

480
00:22:40,650 --> 00:22:43,820
-[thunder rumbling]
-Oh, stomachache.
